<title>Past simple negative form </title>
<sectiontitle>In the negative, we use &lt;i&gt;I/you/he/she/it/we/they + did not&lt;/i&gt; + verb. We usually use the short form &lt;i&gt;didn't. &lt;/i&gt;</sectiontitle>
<titlesound>el_gram_8_1_1.mp3</titlesound>
<text1>I went to work yesterday.</text1>
<text1a>I &lt;b&gt;didn't go&lt;/b&gt; to work yesterday.</text1a>
<sound1>el_gram_8_1_2.mp3</sound1>
<text2>He finished his lunch.</text2>
<text2a>He &lt;b&gt;didn't finish&lt;/b&gt; his lunch.</text2a>
